cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.CE 

This paper deals with the impact of relays on the degrees of freedom (DoF) of wireless networks in the absence of channel state information at the transmitters (CSIT). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also investigates the impact of relays on the X channel and the interference channel, which are both related to network information theory and could fall under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The use of relays to facilitate interference alignment also involves signal processing techniques, which could fall under cs.SI (Signal Processing). The paper also establishes conditions on the number of antennas and relays needed to achieve optimal DoF, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper investigates special cases of the X channel and interference channel, which could fall under cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
